New York University Archives
New York University Archives Collection of Course Bulletins MC.286
126 Linear Feet in 414 bound volumes and 171 boxes
0.34 Gigabytes
1832-2017 The collection consists of publications (bulletins, catalogs, announcements, etc.) that outline the course of study at New York University and its component schools, dating from 1834 to 2017. The publications are a mix of bound and unbound materials, as well as electronic records in the PDF format. They typically include an overview of the school, degree requirements, lists of faculty and administrators, and course descriptions. Early publications sometimes include lists of students and degrees conferred. Materials are in English.
Conditions Governing Access
Materials are open without restrictions.
Conditions Governing Use
Materials in this collection which were created prior to 1924 are in the public domain. Permission to publish or reproduce is not required.
Materials that were published in 1924 or later are potentially protected by copyright and/or related rights. You are free to use materials in the collection in any way that is permitted by the copyright and related rights legislation that applies to your use. For other uses you need to obtain permission from the rights-holder(s).
Existence and Location of Copies
Additional duplicate copies of publications are held in the collection of New York University Publications (preservation copies) (RG 1.0).
Immediate Source of Acquisition
Materials found in collection; provenance is unknown.
Preferred Citation
Identification of item, date; New York University Archives Collection of Course Bulletins; MC 286; box number; folder number; New York University Archives, New York University.
Arrangement
The collection is organized into series based on the New York University Archives's record group classification system. Titles for the record groups are based on the school or program's current official name (as of 2019). For example, School of Commerce bulletins are included as part of the Stern School of Business record group.
Scope and Contents
The collection consists of publications (bulletins, catalogs, announcements, etc.) that outline the course of study at New York University and its component schools, dating from 1834 to 2017. The publications are a mix of bound and unbound materials, as well as electronic records in the PDF format. They typically include an overview of the school, degree requirements, lists of faculty and administrators, and course descriptions. Early publications sometimes include lists of students and degrees conferred.
Processing Information
This collection was assembled by the New York University Archives staff. It was collectively referred to as "Series 3: Bulletins, Catalogs, Announcements" through 2018. This designation may appear on boxes and folders in the current collection.
